21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
22 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of a new law not to be
23 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
24
Req. No. 2069 Page 1

1 This act shall be known and may be cited as the “High Voltage
2 Electric Transmission Facility Act”.
3 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 850 of Title 17, unless there is
5 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 As used in this act:
7 1. “Certificate of authority” means authorization for a
8 transmission developer to comply with the provisions of this act by
9 an order of the Corporation Commission through filing a case with an
10 application, notice, and hearing. The Commission shall establish a
11 unique and identifiable designation for the filing of such cases;
12 2. “Electric transmission facility” means a high-voltage
13 transmission line or high-voltage associated transmission facility
14 with a rating of greater than three hundred (300) kilovolts;
15 3. “FERC” means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission;
16 4. “Transfer” means any sale, assignment, or change in
17 ownership of the electric transmission facility by a transmission
18 developer; and
19 5. “Transmission developer” means any person, firm,
20 corporation, or entity that develops, owns, operates, controls,
21 manages, or maintains an electric transmission facility within this
22 state and is licensed to do business in Oklahoma.
